modules.description: This module handles network communication for IRC clients using Lwt for asynchronous I/O. It provides functions to connect to IRC servers, send and receive messages, and manage socket connections. It works with IPv4 and IPv6 addresses and is used to establish and maintain real-time IRC chat sessions.

This module implements an IRC client with functions to connect to servers, authenticate, and exchange messages asynchronously. It supports operations like joining channels, sending private messages, handling server pings, and maintaining persistent connections with reconnection logic. The module works with IRC connections represented by `connection_t`, handles message parsing, and is used for building real-time IRC bots or chat clients.
